\details{
\subsection{Purpose}{

Signed \verb{/exchange} trading actions: place and modify limit/trigger orders
(single or bulk), open and close positions at market via an aggressive
immediate-or-cancel limit, cancel by order id or client order id (single or
bulk), schedule a dead-man's-switch cancel-all, set per-asset leverage and
isolated margin, and approve an agent (API) wallet or a builder fee. Every
method requires a wallet signing key.

Inherits from \link{HyperliquidBase}. Order/cancel actions are \strong{L1} actions
hashed and signed over the Exchange domain (asset ids and key insertion order
are part of the signature, so both are reproduced exactly). The two
approvals are \strong{user-signed} actions over the \code{HyperliquidSignTransaction}
EIP-712 domain.
}

\subsection{Sync vs Async}{

Most methods support both modes via the \code{async} argument at construction. The
exceptions are \link[=HyperliquidTrading]{market_open()} and
\link[=HyperliquidTrading]{market_close()}: they chain a read (the mid price, and
for closes the open position) before the write, so they are \strong{sync-preferred}
and assume the chained \verb{/info} read resolves synchronously.
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\url{https://hyperliquid.gitbook.io/hyperliquid-docs/for-developers/api/exchange-endpoint}
}

