\subsection{Method \code{approve_agent()}}{
Approve a fresh agent (API) wallet for this account. A new
secp256k1 key is generated locally, its address approved on-chain, and
the \strong{secret is returned to you} -- store it securely, as it is the only
time it is exposed and it can sign trading actions for this account until
revoked.

Mirrors the reference SDK: when \code{name} is \code{NULL} the action is signed with
an empty \code{agentName}. (The SDK then strips the empty field from the posted
body; this client instead posts \code{agentName = ""}, which is
signature-equivalent because the server defaults a missing \code{agentName} to
the empty string -- the EIP-712 digest is identical either way.)
\subsection{Usage}{
\if{html}{\out{<div class="r">}}\preformatted{HyperliquidTrading$approve_agent(name = NULL)}\if{html}{\out{</div>}}
}

\subsection{Arguments}{
\if{html}{\out{<div class="arguments">}}
\describe{
\item{\code{name}}{(scalar<character> | NULL) an optional human-readable agent
name. Default \code{NULL}.}
}
\if{html}{\out{</div>}}
}
\subsection{Returns}{
(promise<data.table>) a single-row \link[data.table:data.table]{data.table::data.table} (or a
promise thereof):
\itemize{
\item agent_address (character) the new agent wallet's \verb{0x} address.
\item agent_key (character) the new agent wallet's hex secret.
\item status (character) the action status (e.g. \code{"ok"}).
}
}
}
